					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13041019#post-4502495</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13041019/scp-5252#post-4502495</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 16 Feb 2020 02:03:46 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>T Rutherford</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4620432</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Much as I enjoyed this in the crit stage, I still feel it needs trimming, especially in the interview sections. You over-detail the visual elements, taking the reader out of the dialogue flow. In future, try to describe the qualities of the scene during natural pauses in the conversation. Let the reader shift more seamlessly between the various sensory elements of a scene, from visual to auditory to ofactory, etc.</p> <p>Beyond that, I really enjoyed this. It dragged on, but the core content kept me invested. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13041019#post-4502411</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13041019/scp-5252#post-4502411</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 16 Feb 2020 00:42:03 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RJB_R</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1229263</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>None of the addenda really vibe with me, the last one really seemed melodramatic and didn’t add anything new. However, the main article body scratched the true crime part of my brain. Even though I didn’t care for the back half, the first half was strong enough that I still upvoted.</p> <p>For future articles, I would recommend leaving a little more of the mystery intact. It’s not as interesting when you go and explain it.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
